ost=900\n  |weight=40\n  |material=dragon hide\n  |reference={{refsrc|src/objects.c|347|unnethack=1986}}}}\n{{armor\n  |color=yellow\n  |name=glowing dragon scales\n  |slot=body armor\n  |ac=1\n  |special=<ul><li>[[light source]]</li></ul>\n  |cost=500\n  |weight=40\n  |material=dragon hide\n  |reference={{refsrc|src/objects.c|365|unnethack=1986}}}}\n'''Glowing dragon scale mail''' is one of two new [[DSM|dragon scale mails]] added in [[UnNetHack]]. By default, glowing dragon scales and glowing dragon scale mail function as [[light source]]s {{refsrc|src/do_wear.c|619|unnethack=1986}}.\n\nPrior to version 5.0.0, the glowing dragon's scales conferred [[petrification resistance]]. As of version 5.0.0, however, the breath types and resistances of all dragons (except the [[Chromatic dragon (UnNetHack)|chromatic dragon]]) are randomized, so the resistance conferred by glowing dragon scales depends on the breath type assigned to the glowing dragon.\n\nNote that in UnNetHack, dragon scale mail is considered a [[magical item]], so it cannot be wished for, according to the [[Wish#UnNetHack|rules for wishing in UnNetHack]]. Dragon scales, however, are acceptable. A note in the source code{{refsrc|src/objects.c|334|unnethack=1986}} explains that this is because magic (a [[scroll of enchant armor]]) is required to produce the mail, but the scales are produced \"naturally\". Also, it is possible to wish for the scales that produce a specific resistance only if the appearance of that type is known, but it is possible to wish for scales from any dragon regardless of whether its resistance is known. Because \"glowing dragon\" is an appearance, glowing dragon scales can be wished for without knowing what resistance they give.\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Dragon armor]]\n[[Category:UnNetHack]]"}